## Example environment file

### A comma-separated list of domains to blocklist for when scraping
WEBSCRAPER_BLACKLIST="google.com,google.be"

### A comma separated list of twitter credentials to use
TWITTER_ACCOUNTS="foo:bar,foo:baz"

### A comma separated list of twitter Bearer API tokens to use. Takes precedence over TWITTER_ACCOUNTS
TWITTER_API_KEYS="apikey1,apikey2"

### LinkedIn Authentication
# You can get these values from your browser's developer tools after logging into LinkedIn:
# 1. Open LinkedIn in your browser and log in
# 2. Open Developer Tools (F12)
# 3. Go to Application/Storage > Cookies
# 4. Find and copy the values for:

# li_at cookie - Your LinkedIn session cookie
LINKEDIN_LI_AT_COOKIE="your_li_at_cookie_here"

# CSRF Token - Can be found in requests as 'csrf-token' header
LINKEDIN_CSRF_TOKEN="your_csrf_token_here"

# JSESSIONID - Session ID cookie (optional but recommended)
LINKEDIN_JSESSIONID="your_jsessionid_here"

### Listening address
LISTEN_ADDRESS=":8080"
